<odoo>
    <record id="view_res_config_settings_pepadocs" model="ir.ui.view">
        <field name="name">res.config.settings.view.pepadocs</field>
        <field name="model">res.config.settings</field>
        <field name="inherit_id" ref="base.res_config_settings_view_form"/>
        <field name="arch" type="xml">
            <xpath expr="//div[hasclass('settings')]" position="inside">
                <div class="app_settings_block" data-string="Pepadocs Settings" string="Pepadocs"  data-key="pepadocs">
                    <h2>Pepadocs parameters</h2>
                    <div class="row mt16 o_settings_container">
                        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 o_setting_box">
                            <div class="o_setting_right_pane">
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>1. Go to pepadocs, create an account, then create an entity. </span>
                                    <a href="https://pepadocs.com/inscription" target="_blank">Inscription Pepadocs</a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>2. In your entity panel, go to Panel - General configuration - Website / Collaboration space. Then fill in the required information to create your pepadocs subdomain.</span>
                                </div>
                                <span class="o_form_label">Subdomain (e.g. mycompany.pepadocs.com)</span>
                                <field name="pepadocs_webdomain"/>
                                <br />
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>3. Get your API info under "Connectors and APIs" in your entity panel menu:</span>
                                </div>
                                <span class="o_form_label">API id</span>
                                <field name="pepadocs_id"/>
                                <br />
                                <span class="o_form_label">API Key</span>
                                <field name="pepadocs_key" widget="password"/>
                                <br />
                                <span class="o_form_label">API Public ID</span>
                                <field name="pepadocs_idPage"/>
                                <br />
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>4. Once the configuration has been saved here, load the odoo Pepadocs application and click on the refresh button. Then reload the page.</span>
                                </div>
                                <br />
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>5. You can now create your report templates and manage them from the Odoo Pepadocs application. You can also use the Pepadocs mobile application to complete your documents.</span>
                                </div>
                                <br />
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>Don't forget to click on Refresh in the Odoo Pepadocs application when you modify your templates or settings.</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 o_setting_box">
                            <div class="o_setting_right_pane">
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>In the profile of your odoo users (not your employees), you can indicate their Pepadocs id. If you want each employee to connect his or her own pepadocs account to Odoo, enable this option.</span>
                                    <span class="o_form_label">Enable employee synchronization</span>
                                    <field name="pepadocs_autoSyncEmployees"/>
                                    <br />
                                </div>
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>You can also define a pepadocs group to which new employees who connect their own account to Pepadocs are added. To do this, enter the group id. (Find the group id by looking at the url: https://monentreprise.pepadocs.com/fr/config/ModoGroups/Group-group_29 and so 29 is the id). This will only work when an employee synchronizes himself to pepadocs.</span>
                                    <span class="o_form_label">default group id</span>
                                    <field name="pepadocs_syncWithModoGroupId"/>
                                    <br />
                                </div>
                                <div class="text-muted">
                                    <span>To remove an employee's access to Pepadocs, remove them from all your pepadocs groups. (However, if automatic synchronization is enabled and the employee still has an Odoo account with you, he or she will be able to recreate a synchronized pepadocs account.)</span>
                                    <br /><br />
                                    <span>More help can be found <a target="_blank" href="https://pepadocs.com/en/guides/category/odoo-with-pepadocs-62">here</a> or by email <a href="mailto:contact@nexswiss.ch">contact@nexswiss.ch</a></span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </xpath>
        </field>
    </record>

    <record id="action_pepadocs_config" model="ir.actions.act_window">
        <field name="name">Pepadocs Config</field>
        <field name="type">ir.actions.act_window</field>
        <field name="res_model">res.config.settings</field>
        <field name="view_mode">form</field>
        <field name="target">inline</field>
        <field name="context">{'module' : 'pepadocs'}</field>
    </record>

    <menuitem id="menu_pepadocs_config"
          name="Pepadocs Settings"
          parent="base.menu_config"
          action="action_pepadocs_config"
          sequence="1"/>
</odoo>